-- Coca-Cola Icecek Rises After Pledging to Pay Dividend May 25
-- B y   M a r k   B e n t l e y
-- 2012-05-22T15:32:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-22/coca-cola-icecek-rises-after-pledging-to-pay-dividend-may-25-1-.html
Coca-Cola Icecek AS (CCOLA) , the bottler of
cola drinks, gained in Istanbul after saying it will pay a gross
dividend of 0.24 liras per share on May 25.  Coca-Cola Icecek climbed as much as 9.5 percent to a record
high before paring gains to 4.6 percent and closing at 24.90
liras, its strongest in almost a month. The company made the
statement on the dividend to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange  after
markets closed yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Bentley in Istanbul at 
 mbentley3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
